00:01:26.252 --> 00:01:27.879 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:01:34.094 --> 00:01:35.512 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Wait.

00:01:35.595 --> 00:01:37.639 position:50% align:center
Are you telling me that you
don't swim for the college?

00:01:37.722 --> 00:01:41.142 position:50% align:center
'Fraid not. I mean, they don't
even have a swim club, so...

00:01:41.226 --> 00:01:44.020 position:50% align:center
But you worked so hard
at it in high school.

00:01:44.104 --> 00:01:45.438 position:50% align:center
It's cool.

00:01:45.522 --> 00:01:48.400 position:50% align:center
There's a ton of other awesome
stuff to do in college.

00:01:48.483 --> 00:01:50.318 position:50% align:center
I bet.

00:01:50.402 --> 00:01:53.446 position:50% align:center
Well, guess I'll find out soon!

00:01:53.530 --> 00:01:55.865 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Little did I realize...

00:01:57.450 --> 00:01:58.868 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Is he...

00:02:01.371 --> 00:02:02.997 position:50% align:center
...sleeping?

00:02:07.377 --> 00:02:09.337 position:50% align:center
What the what...?

00:02:12.132 --> 00:02:14.175 position:50% align:center
No, seriously, what?

00:02:16.886 --> 00:02:19.097 position:50% align:center
What in the actual what?

00:02:26.104 --> 00:02:27.439 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Let's be real.

00:02:27.522 --> 00:02:31.151 position:50% align:center
I kind of assumed the year
might turn out like this.

00:02:31.234 --> 00:02:32.819 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:02:36.281 --> 00:02:37.741 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI yawns]

00:02:37.824 --> 00:02:41.202 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Sakurai!

00:02:41.286 --> 00:02:43.997 position:50% align:center
Whoa! I overshot ya! Ha, ha.

00:02:45.999 --> 00:02:48.335 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:02:48.418 --> 00:02:51.463 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah, hi. Uzaki, right?

00:02:51.546 --> 00:02:53.506 position:50% align:center
All alone again, I see.

00:02:53.590 --> 00:02:55.675 position:50% align:center
I'll just have to
hang out with you, then!

00:02:55.759 --> 00:02:59.679 position:50% align:center
Your college-loner lifestyle
is officially ending today!

00:04:35.442 --> 00:04:36.693 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE STUDENT A]
What's up for lunch?

00:04:36.776 --> 00:04:39.446 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE STUDENT B]
Uh. The Dining hall, I guess.

00:04:39.529 --> 00:04:41.281 position:50% align:center
[MALE STUDENT A]
Hey, is it cool if we join?

00:04:42.532 --> 00:04:47.537 position:50% align:center
Wow. Canceled.
Guess my afternoon's wide open.

00:04:47.620 --> 00:04:50.707 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Sakurai!

00:04:50.790 --> 00:04:54.336 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] No work today, either.
What to do...?

00:04:54.419 --> 00:04:55.670 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:04:55.754 --> 00:04:58.006 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE STUDENT C yelps]
What was with that glare?

00:04:58.089 --> 00:04:59.466 position:50% align:center
He's scary.

00:04:59.549 --> 00:05:02.719 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Sakurai!

00:05:02.802 --> 00:05:05.847 position:50% align:center
Maybe I'll just bum around
on my own for once. 

00:05:05.930 --> 00:05:07.474 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] It's like I can't
even get any quiet time

00:05:07.557 --> 00:05:10.185 position:50% align:center
now that she shows up
every five minutes.

00:05:10.268 --> 00:05:12.228 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Sakurai!

00:05:12.312 --> 00:05:15.065 position:50% align:center
[exhales]
What am I always telling you?

00:05:15.148 --> 00:05:16.649 position:50% align:center
There's no reason
for you to yell--

00:05:16.733 --> 00:05:19.611 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI chuckles]

00:05:19.694 --> 00:05:21.029 position:50% align:center
Well, I called you
over and over,

00:05:21.112 --> 00:05:22.530 position:50% align:center
but you weren't hearing me!

00:05:22.614 --> 00:05:24.491 position:50% align:center
So, what's up?
Where are ya goin'?

00:05:24.574 --> 00:05:27.243 position:50% align:center
Uzaki, seriously, what the
hell is wrong with you?

00:05:27.327 --> 00:05:28.203 position:50% align:center
Huh? Nothing!

00:05:28.286 --> 00:05:29.996 position:50% align:center
Wait, are you headed to lunch?

00:05:30.080 --> 00:05:31.581 position:50% align:center
Aw, man, that's too bad.

00:05:31.664 --> 00:05:33.500 position:50% align:center
My friends and I
actually already ate.

00:05:33.583 --> 00:05:35.669 position:50% align:center
But if you insist, I could
always come along

00:05:35.752 --> 00:05:38.254 position:50% align:center
to keep you company and watch
you eat. How's that sound?

00:05:38.338 --> 00:05:40.340 position:50% align:center
I've got no classes
this afternoon.

00:05:40.423 --> 00:05:43.176 position:50% align:center
I was just taking a little
stroll around campus.

00:05:43.259 --> 00:05:44.678 position:50% align:center
Later.

00:05:50.975 --> 00:05:53.853 position:50% align:center
Uzaki. Is there a reason
you're following me?

00:05:53.937 --> 00:05:55.689 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Yikes, look at that face!

00:05:55.772 --> 00:05:56.898 position:50% align:center
Well, as it turns out,

00:05:56.981 --> 00:05:59.442 position:50% align:center
I'm suddenly available
this afternoon, too!

00:05:59.526 --> 00:06:01.027 position:50% align:center
Crazy, right?

00:06:01.111 --> 00:06:02.278 position:50% align:center
Given half the chance,

00:06:02.362 --> 00:06:04.489 position:50% align:center
I know you tend to default
to being a loner.

00:06:04.572 --> 00:06:07.534 position:50% align:center
But, c'mon, two has got to be
way more fun than one!

00:06:07.617 --> 00:06:08.952 position:50% align:center
Not your business.

00:06:09.035 --> 00:06:10.745 position:50% align:center
Besides, I've told you
a million times,

00:06:10.829 --> 00:06:13.790 position:50% align:center
I happen to find quiet time
alone much more relaxing.

00:06:13.873 --> 00:06:16.918 position:50% align:center
Here we go again.
Being a loner is no fun!

00:06:17.002 --> 00:06:18.169 position:50% align:center
Don't call me that.

00:06:18.253 --> 00:06:19.713 position:50% align:center
Hey, that's right!

00:06:19.796 --> 00:06:22.215 position:50% align:center
You're actually not a loner,
because I'm here with you now!

00:06:22.298 --> 00:06:24.718 position:50% align:center
Quit tagging along,
you damn pest!

00:06:24.801 --> 00:06:26.511 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:06:26.594 --> 00:06:27.887 position:50% align:center
Are ya nervous?

00:06:27.971 --> 00:06:30.724 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
What? No!

00:06:30.807 --> 00:06:32.434 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Well, then. Where are we going?

00:06:32.517 --> 00:06:33.476 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Not telling.

00:06:33.560 --> 00:06:34.728 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Bowling? Karaoke?

00:06:34.811 --> 00:06:35.603 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Forget it.

00:06:35.687 --> 00:06:37.856 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Aw, c'mon, spill it!

00:06:37.939 --> 00:06:38.565 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
No.

00:06:38.648 --> 00:06:39.858 position:50% align:center
Ugh! What's with you?

00:06:39.941 --> 00:06:41.985 position:50% align:center
Why're you being so rude today?

00:06:42.068 --> 00:06:43.403 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
I'm in the mood.

00:06:43.486 --> 00:06:44.988 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
In the mood?!

00:06:46.781 --> 00:06:50.702 position:50% align:center
What's the deal? We've hung
out before, so why not now?

00:06:50.785 --> 00:06:51.953 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:06:52.037 --> 00:06:53.788 position:50% align:center
Treating me differently
depending on your mood?

00:06:53.872 --> 00:06:56.291 position:50% align:center
It must be so convenient
that you can get with me

00:06:56.374 --> 00:06:58.877 position:50% align:center
when you feel like it and
otherwise it's bye-bye!

00:06:58.960 --> 00:07:00.253 position:50% align:center
Can you please
watch your phrasing

00:07:00.337 --> 00:07:02.505 position:50% align:center
when there are other
people around?

00:07:02.589 --> 00:07:03.590 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:03.673 --> 00:07:04.716 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE STUDENT E]
What a jerk!

00:07:04.799 --> 00:07:05.842 position:50% align:center
[FEMALE STUDENT F]
Utter trash.

00:07:05.925 --> 00:07:06.968 position:50% align:center
[MALE STUDENT B]
Dude.

00:07:07.052 --> 00:07:09.012 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:07:09.095 --> 00:07:11.097 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:07:11.181 --> 00:07:13.683 position:50% align:center
Okay, fine, I suck!
Come on, let's go.

00:07:13.767 --> 00:07:15.352 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Woo-hoo!

00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:20.273 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Hey, once we're done here,

00:07:20.357 --> 00:07:22.442 position:50% align:center
what do you say
we get some food?

00:07:22.525 --> 00:07:25.445 position:50% align:center
I'd totally be down to join you
for dinner if you want me to.

00:07:25.528 --> 00:07:26.821 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
I'm not paying.

00:07:26.905 --> 00:07:28.365 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Freakin' cheapskate.

00:07:28.448 --> 00:07:30.742 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Why? You tryin'
to mooch or what?

00:07:33.828 --> 00:07:35.163 position:50% align:center
Wait, you're kidding me.

00:07:35.246 --> 00:07:37.749 position:50% align:center
Were you really gonna see
a movie by yourself today?

00:07:37.832 --> 00:07:39.793 position:50% align:center
Sure. Why not?

00:07:41.127 --> 00:07:43.546 position:50% align:center
[laughs]
Solo date!

00:07:43.630 --> 00:07:45.382 position:50% align:center
Tsk! What's so funny?

00:07:45.465 --> 00:07:47.175 position:50% align:center
Wow, you're that guy!

00:07:47.258 --> 00:07:48.635 position:50% align:center
[laughing continues]

00:07:48.718 --> 00:07:50.595 position:50% align:center
I mean, that's a
prime loner move!

00:07:50.679 --> 00:07:52.931 position:50% align:center
It's right up there with
going solo at a water park

00:07:53.014 --> 00:07:54.724 position:50% align:center
or a sushi buffet!

00:07:54.808 --> 00:07:56.267 position:50% align:center
Ha! I can't!

00:07:56.351 --> 00:07:57.977 position:50% align:center
Why don't you ever shut up?

00:07:58.061 --> 00:08:00.897 position:50% align:center
You're gonna start making
enemies everywhere you go.

00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:03.900 position:50% align:center
At the very least, you could
bring it down a notch.

00:08:03.983 --> 00:08:06.903 position:50% align:center
Listen, this is the
"live and let live " era.

00:08:06.986 --> 00:08:08.822 position:50% align:center
We're all free to find
time in our busy day

00:08:08.905 --> 00:08:11.241 position:50% align:center
to see the movie we
want the way we want.

00:08:11.324 --> 00:08:12.534 position:50% align:center
Right. Sure.

00:08:12.617 --> 00:08:14.703 position:50% align:center
Seriously, shouldn't we
all spend our free time

00:08:14.786 --> 00:08:16.204 position:50% align:center
however we choose to?

00:08:16.287 --> 00:08:17.747 position:50% align:center
Don't laugh at other
people's hobbies

00:08:17.831 --> 00:08:19.165 position:50% align:center
just cuz they're not yours.

00:08:19.249 --> 00:08:20.709 position:50% align:center
Yeah, 'kay.

00:08:20.792 --> 00:08:23.545 position:50% align:center
Plenty of people treat movies
just like any other pastime.

00:08:23.628 --> 00:08:25.255 position:50% align:center
Not everyone makes a
big deal about whether

00:08:25.338 --> 00:08:27.173 position:50% align:center
someone's in the
seat next to them.

00:08:27.257 --> 00:08:28.550 position:50% align:center
That's just how it is.

00:08:28.633 --> 00:08:30.176 position:50% align:center
Totally get it.

00:08:31.261 --> 00:08:33.179 position:50% align:center
Spoken like a true loner!

00:08:33.263 --> 00:08:36.558 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Give me the strength
to keep it together.

00:08:36.641 --> 00:08:38.518 position:50% align:center
Going to a movie whenever
one feels like it

00:08:38.601 --> 00:08:40.770 position:50% align:center
doesn't make one a loner.

00:08:40.854 --> 00:08:44.190 position:50% align:center
The scheduling alone is a hassle
with more people in the mix.

00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:46.151 position:50% align:center
Oh, that's a fair point.

00:08:46.234 --> 00:08:48.486 position:50% align:center
The main bummer, though,
is that you can't talk spoilers

00:08:48.570 --> 00:08:51.197 position:50% align:center
with your friends really loudly
afterwards when you go alone!

00:08:51.281 --> 00:08:53.658 position:50% align:center
Okay, you know that's, like,
one of the worst possible

00:08:53.742 --> 00:08:56.161 position:50% align:center
things you can do as a
human being, right?

00:08:57.537 --> 00:09:00.665 position:50% align:center
Say no more. I get it. I do.

00:09:00.749 --> 00:09:02.792 position:50% align:center
You're just determined
to soldier on

00:09:02.876 --> 00:09:05.462 position:50% align:center
despite your
desperate loneliness.

00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:08.006 position:50% align:center
Don't act like you've
figured me out.

00:09:08.089 --> 00:09:10.842 position:50% align:center
Honestly. I knew I shouldn't
have brought you.

00:09:10.925 --> 00:09:12.052 position:50% align:center
Well, it wouldn't have mattered,

00:09:12.135 --> 00:09:14.804 position:50% align:center
cuz I'd follow you all
sneaky-like, anyway.

00:09:14.888 --> 00:09:16.973 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI groans]

00:09:17.057 --> 00:09:18.767 position:50% align:center
You are so messed up.

00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:21.353 position:50% align:center
I guess that's really
your idea of fun?

00:09:21.436 --> 00:09:22.812 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:09:22.896 --> 00:09:24.105 position:50% align:center
Think about it.

00:09:24.189 --> 00:09:25.857 position:50% align:center
It'd be all kinds of
hilarious if I spotted you

00:09:25.940 --> 00:09:28.234 position:50% align:center
buying something embarrassing
in some weird store!

00:09:28.318 --> 00:09:30.278 position:50% align:center
I know I'd laugh myself
silly if I saw you

00:09:30.362 --> 00:09:32.572 position:50% align:center
picking out dirty
DVDs or whatever!

00:09:32.655 --> 00:09:34.199 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI laughs]

00:09:34.282 --> 00:09:35.992 position:50% align:center
Owie, that hurts, stop that!

00:09:36.076 --> 00:09:36.951 position:50% align:center
Sakurai!

00:09:37.035 --> 00:09:38.078 position:50% align:center
Uncle, uncle, uncle!

00:09:38.161 --> 00:09:41.081 position:50% align:center
Uncle, uncle, uncle! Ugh!

00:09:41.164 --> 00:09:43.375 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] College students
are actual adults,

00:09:43.458 --> 00:09:46.044 position:50% align:center
so no more mean-girl mocking
of people's hobbies

00:09:46.127 --> 00:09:47.754 position:50% align:center
or digging into
their private lives!

00:09:47.837 --> 00:09:49.506 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
I'm sorry!

00:09:49.589 --> 00:09:51.299 position:50% align:center
Finally.

00:09:51.383 --> 00:09:53.093 position:50% align:center
I haven't been able to
pick which movie to see

00:09:53.176 --> 00:09:54.969 position:50% align:center
with you all up in my business.

00:09:55.053 --> 00:09:59.099 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI groans] Hold on, you came
without a movie in mind?

00:09:59.182 --> 00:10:01.476 position:50% align:center
Well, it was a
last-minute thing.

00:10:01.559 --> 00:10:04.854 position:50% align:center
Besides, choosing here is one
of the thrills of solo movies.

00:10:07.857 --> 00:10:09.734 position:50% align:center
You sure about that?

00:10:13.279 --> 00:10:15.532 position:50% align:center
[sighs]

00:10:15.615 --> 00:10:17.409 position:50% align:center
[grunts]

00:10:19.994 --> 00:10:21.162 position:50% align:center
Listen.

00:10:21.246 --> 00:10:22.414 position:50% align:center
Yes?

00:10:22.497 --> 00:10:24.040 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] If there's one
you wanna see, I'll pay.

00:10:24.124 --> 00:10:26.918 position:50% align:center
Really? What about
your solo movie?

00:10:27.002 --> 00:10:30.046 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] It's not, like,
a rule that I have to go solo.

00:10:30.130 --> 00:10:31.381 position:50% align:center
And actually, with you here,

00:10:31.464 --> 00:10:34.050 position:50% align:center
maybe I'll see
something different.

00:10:34.134 --> 00:10:37.220 position:50% align:center
Anyway. I figure my reward
points will cover the two of us.

00:10:37.303 --> 00:10:38.805 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Seriously?

00:10:38.888 --> 00:10:42.434 position:50% align:center
Well, if you say so, then I'll
totally let you treat! Thanks!

00:10:42.517 --> 00:10:44.644 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
How about...

00:10:44.728 --> 00:10:46.146 position:50% align:center
This! What a bargain!

00:10:46.229 --> 00:10:48.148 position:50% align:center
I mean, it's heroes as
far as the eye can see,

00:10:48.231 --> 00:10:49.733 position:50% align:center
so we really can't lose!

00:10:49.816 --> 00:10:51.526 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah, that's a great one.

00:10:51.609 --> 00:10:54.696 position:50% align:center
I saw it once, but I was
thinking of seeing it again.

00:10:54.779 --> 00:10:56.656 position:50% align:center
Oh, cool!

00:10:57.741 --> 00:11:00.076 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI] Two students, please.
I'll use my points.

00:11:00.160 --> 00:11:02.996 position:50% align:center
Yes, certainly.
I'd be happy to help you.

00:11:03.079 --> 00:11:05.707 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Well, she has her moments,

00:11:05.790 --> 00:11:07.542 position:50% align:center
but she still makes me crazy.

00:11:07.625 --> 00:11:11.087 position:50% align:center
She seems happy, though,
so I guess I can do this much.

00:11:11.171 --> 00:11:13.048 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Mm-hm.

00:11:14.215 --> 00:11:15.550 position:50% align:center
[UZAKI]
Hey, by the way.

00:11:15.633 --> 00:11:16.634 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Hm?

00:11:16.718 --> 00:11:18.011 position:50% align:center
Heh...

00:11:18.094 --> 00:11:19.929 position:50% align:center
It's interesting that you've
apparently seen enough

00:11:20.013 --> 00:11:22.265 position:50% align:center
